  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/SBQ.jpg?itok=EgJFkO4b",
  "bio_raw": "Dr Sarkar Barbaq Quarmal is currently an Associate Professor and Graduate Program Coordinator at the Department of Media Studies and Journalism. He completed both his undergraduate and graduate studies in Mass Communication from University of Rajshahi, and earned his PhD from Ibaraki University, Japan. Before joining ULAB in September 2013, Dr Quarmal worked as a post-doctoral researcher at Ibaraki University, Japan. Among his notable contributions in recent years include the Bangladesh Chapter in SAGE International Encyclopedia of Mass Media and Society, co-authoring the book Gender Representation in Bangladeshi Media and its Influence on Youth with Prof. Jude Genilo and Dr Mohammad Shazzad Hossain and formulation of a white paper on OTT regulations in Bangladesh with Prof. Jude Genilo and Dr Muhammad Abdul Kader. His research interests include ICT in Communication and Development, Media Studies, New Media, Communication for Development, Social Network Analysis etc.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "ICT in Communication and Development, Media Studies, New Media, Communication for Development, Social Network Analysis etc."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD in Energy and Risk Science from Ibaraki University, Japan\nMSS in Mass Communication and Journalism from University of Rajshahi, Bangladesh\nBSS in Mass Communication and Journalism from University of Rajshahi, Bangladesh"
    }
  ],
